You've been making wise choices all day, but then bedtime comes around, and suddenly you’re standing in front of the fridge or pantry grabbing anything you can get your hands on.⁣⁣

Can you relate?⁣⁣

Snacking within 3-4 hours of bedtime can wake you up in the middle of the night because of blood sugar (too high or low), and then you have a sleepless night, and the whole cycle repeats itself. People who haven't slept well tend to eat more the next day. And sometimes, sugar cravings are a sign of dehydration.⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Try these tips to avoid going overboard with a bedtime snack. Let us know if it helps.⁣⁣

In the colder months, we tend to stay indoors more, exercise less, and crave warm comfort foods. If you can relate, then consider these 7 ways to detox your winter tendencies and boost your health’s resiliency!⁣
⁣
REDUCE INDOOR AIR POLLUTION - Minimize using fireplaces, and burning candles.⁣
⁣
AVOID ARTIFICIAL SCENTS - Synthetic fragrances are formulated with a variety of chemicals that may not be safe. Furthermore, inhaling these chemical formulas provides a fast route into our bodies.⁣
⁣
FRESH AIR - Ventilate when cooking. Consider opportunities to open windows, especially after burning candles, and fireplaces, and using products with artificial scents. Air purifiers can reduce toxic exposures too.⁣
⁣
REMOVE DUST - Vacuuming and wiping surfaces with a wet microfiber cloth should be done regularly to minimize exposure.⁣
⁣
EXERCISE - Sweat regularly. Sweating helps to rid your body of waste.⁣
⁣
BOOST IMMUNITY - Wonderful nutrient-dense diets for the winter include soups and vegetable-rich dishes. Organic herbal teas also support immunity, detoxification, and sleep.⁣
⁣
EPSOM SALT BATHS - Baths can help detox your body. Afterward, hydrate your skin with a non-toxic moisturizer!⁣
⁣

Stressful times can lead to feelings of anxiety. Whether yours is mild or severe (panic attacks) there is a lot you can do to help manage it.⁣
⁣
Here are some natural methods that may help:⁣
⁣
Certain lifestyle choices like eating whole foods, getting enough sleep, and practicing mindfulness and meditation can help.⁣
⁣
Holy basil/tulsi: This adaptogen works with your body to give you just what you need. If you're stressed, it can help calm you. Tired? It can energize you.⁣
⁣
Maca: Can help to balance moods.⁣
⁣
Goji berries: These delicious berries can be eaten dried or you can add goji berry powder to a smoothie. They have a lot of health benefits including improving mood.⁣
⁣
Reishi Mushrooms: These mushrooms are calming and can help improve sleep. We can cope a lot better when we are well-rested.⁣
⁣
Rhodiola: Can strengthen the nervous system so it can recover from stressful situations easier.⁣
⁣
Ginseng: Calms the mind.⁣
⁣
Licorice Root: Nourishes the adrenal glands. These small glands sit on top of your kidneys and have an important role in producing stress hormones and sex hormones when we enter perimenopause and menopause. If our adrenals are worn out women tend to experience more anxiety, mood swings, sleep disturbances, and hot flashes during this time.⁣
⁣
Ashwagandha: Also an adaptogen, ashwagandha helps to reduce cortisol (the body’s stress hormone) and in turn helps relieve anxiety⁣
⁣
Cordyceps: Helps when you are struggling with fatigue and can improve endurance.⁣
⁣

About 80% of the population today experience back pain on a daily basis. There are a lot of natural ways to relieve your back pain and these ways are proven and tested by many actual people who experience tremendous back pain. Below are 9 natural remedies to help soothe back pain.⁣
⁣
LIMIT BED REST - It’s recommended to be more active rather than less as long as it doesn't exacerbate the pain.⁣
⁣
ICE FIRST, HEAT LATER - Always apply cold or ice before the heating pads, especially if there is swelling.⁣
⁣
TAKE A HOT BATH - When your body absorbs the heat from your hot bath, the muscles tend to relax. Adding Epsom salts, rich in magnesium helps with further muscle tension.⁣
⁣
GET REGULAR MASSAGES - According to studies, it is seen that people who get regular massages have a much lower percentage of experiencing extreme pain and stress in their back.⁣
⁣
A GOOD DIET - choose to consume many foods that have anti-inflammatory properties like flax and chia seeds, green leafy vegetables, and fruits.⁣
⁣
PERFECT YOUR POSTURE - Once you've trained your body and back, you will notice an improvement in your discomfort level. Try putting a book on top of your head and balancing it as you walk, sit, and stand.⁣
⁣
PHYSICAL THERAPY - Your therapist would be able to guide you through activities that will help strengthen your back weaknesses and ideally experience less pain in the future.⁣
⁣
STRENGTH TRAINING - Strengthening your core muscles can improve your posture and in turn, can also help you relieve your back pain.⁣
⁣
ACUPUNCTURE - The needles help release stagnant energy that can be leading to pain in your back from other parts of your body.⁣

Buy a HEPA air filter to clean the air.⁣
Open your windows to bring in fresher outdoor air.⁣

Baking soda actually comes from a mineral called natron. Natron is rich in sodium bicarbonate, a term commonly used for baking soda. One of baking soda's greatest strengths is as a neutralizer, which means it helps maintain the acid-base balance in the body. The pH value expresses the level of acidity or alkalinity in the body, with 7 being the neutral value. When values go too far in either direction, human health suffers.⁣
⁣
If you eat foods that are highly acidic (e.g., meats, dairy, chocolate, most grains) and don't balance them with those that are more alkaline, then you may find yourself reaching for the bicarbonate! The fact that the biological life functions best in a non-acidic (alkaline) environment speaks miles about the usefulness of baking soda.⁣
⁣
HEALING POWERS OF BAKING SODA:⁣
⁣
ALLERGY & CHEMICAL SENSITIVITY RELIEF - According to Dr. Eric Chan (in Sircus' book), the use of a sodium bicarbonate IV can stop allergic reactions and consuming a drink that contains baking soda can reduce symptoms of chemical sensitivity.⁣
⁣
ULCERS & G.I. PROBLEMS - According to @drmercola, 1 to 2 teaspoons of baking soda stirred into 8 ounces of water is an effective way to deal with ulcer pain.⁣
⁣
BODY ODOR - You can avoid body odor and the nasty chemicals in commercial antiperspirants and deodorants by combining baking soda and water to make a paste. Apply a thin layer.⁣
⁣
ITCHINESS - You can rub either dry baking soda or a paste made with water on insect bites, poison ivy, or itchy rashes to reduce the itching.⁣
⁣
PLAQUE BUSTER - Helps eliminate tooth plaque and fight oral bacteria.⁣

There are many factors that affect our ability to absorb or utilize nutrients from the foods we eat, including stress, physical trauma & environmental pollutants.⁣
⁣
7 COMMON NUTRIENT DEFICIENCIES:⁣
⁣
CALCIUM—Too little calcium can cause muscle weakness, fatigue, muscle spasms and cramps, numbness and tingling in the fingers and toes, wheezing, and difficulty swallowing.⁣
⁣
IRON—Low levels of iron are associated with anemia, a disorder characterized by fatigue, brittle nails, paleness, and shortness of breath. Too little iron is also associated with dizziness, headache, sensitivity to cold, and poor attention span.⁣
⁣
MAGNESIUM—Low magnesium is associated with nausea, weakness, vomiting, fatigue, migraine, asthma, osteoporosis, high blood pressure, type 2 diabetes, and metabolic syndrome.⁣
⁣
OMEGA-3—An omega-3 deficiency can be marked by joint pain, dry skin, brittle nails, trouble concentrating, and mood swings.⁣
⁣
VITAMIN A—This vitamin deficiency is associated with vision problems, including blindness.⁣
⁣
VITAMIN B12—Deficiency symptoms include anemia, fatigue, loss of appetite, weight loss, weakness, constipation, numbness, and tingling in the hands and feet, depression, and balance problems.⁣
⁣
VITAMIN D—Deficiency symptoms often take time to appear and go unnoticed until something occurs, such as a fracture or a diagnosis of bone loss or osteoporosis⁣
⁣
Implementing the above nutritional tips along with high-quality nutritional supplements can help get you back on track!⁣

Baking soda actually comes from a mineral called natron. Natron is rich in sodium bicarbonate, a term commonly used for baking soda. One of baking soda's greatest strengths is as a neutralizer, which means it helps maintain the acid-base balance in the body. The pH value expresses the level of acidity or alkalinity in the body, with 7 being the neutral value. When values go too far in either direction, human health suffers.⁣
⁣
If you eat foods that are highly acidic (e.g., meats, dairy, chocolate, most grains) and don't balance them with those that are more alkaline, then you may find yourself reaching for the bicarbonate! The fact that the biological life functions best in a non-acidic (alkaline) environment speaks miles about the usefulness of baking soda.⁣
⁣
HEALING POWERS OF BAKING SODA:⁣
⁣
ALLERGY & CHEMICAL SENSITIVITY RELIEF - According to Dr. Eric Chan (in Sircus' book), the use of a sodium bicarbonate IV can stop allergic reactions and consuming a drink that contains baking soda can reduce symptoms of chemical sensitivity.⁣

ULCERS & G.I PROBLEMS - According to @drmercola, 1 to 2 teaspoons of baking soda stirred into 8 ounces of water is an effective way to deal with ulcer pain.⁣

BODY ODOR - You can avoid body odor and the nasty chemicals in commercial antiperspirants and deodorants by combining baking soda and water to make a paste. Apply a thin layer.⁣

ITCHINESS - You can rub either dry baking soda or a paste made with water on insect bites, poison ivy, or itchy rashes to reduce the itching.⁣

PLAQUE BUSTER - Helps eliminate tooth plaque and fight oral bacteria.⁣

Want to get the most benefits from your supplements? Quality and timing are key! Start with quality products made by reputable manufacturers, and take your supplements at the right time. ⁣
⁣
Here's a guide to supplement timing:⁣
⁣
Morning: Take vitamins E and CoQ10 with healthy fats like avocado or coconut oil. B vitamins can be taken with or without food. Take CoQ10 with caution if you have diabetes or low blood pressure. Take iron on an empty stomach and never with calcium. Take vitamin C with iron to improve absorption.⁣
⁣
Afternoon: Take fish oil with food. Take iodine for a midday energy boost. Take vitamin D with healthy fats like avocado or olive oil. Take vitamin K with a healthy fat and avoid taking it with other fat-soluble vitamins. Take zinc with food but never with calcium or iron.⁣
⁣
Evening: Take calcium at night and avoid taking high doses with zinc or magnesium. Take magnesium before retiring to help you relax and fall asleep. Take probiotics before retiring for best results. Take turmeric at least three hours before or after a meal.⁣
⁣
Remember: take multivitamins with a meal to prevent nausea, and don't take antioxidant supplements and calcium supplements together. Avoid taking large amounts of mineral supplements at the same time. If you're a green or black tea drinker, allow a few hours between consuming the tea and taking iron supplements.⁣
